# Quickstart

Install the package from PyPI:

```console
$ python -m pip install {{ repo_name }}
```

Or with uv:

```console
$ uv add {{ repo_name }}
```

## Import

```python
import {{ package_name }}
```

## Development install

Clone the repository and sync the development environment:

```console
$ git clone {{ repository_url }}
$ cd {{ repo_name }}
$ just dev
```

Run checks and coverage with:

```console
$ just check
$ just coverage
```

Build the documentation locally with:

```console
$ just docs
```

Build and serve the documentation locally with:

```console
$ just docs-serve
```

The local server prints the URL, by default `http://127.0.0.1:8000/`. If that port is already in use, it tries the next available port.
